Up  to 8 alleged militants belived to be senoir commanders of a Taliban faction were killed and 2-4 injured in a strike on a vehicle.
7 unknown alleged militants killed and 3 injured in a strike on a vehicle in the borderlands of North and South Waziristan.
A Miranshah house destroyed killing 4 alleged militants.
3-6 alleged militants killed and up to 3 injured on a strike on an ex-girl's school in Miranshah.
Up to 10 killed and one injured in a strike. Disputes on wether the dead were militants or civilians.
4-5 alleged militants killed and several injured in a strike on a house in Datte Khel Kalai.
Up tp 12 killed and 3 injured, mostly civilians, after a strike hit a house and a nearby mosque during morning prayers.
3-4 alleged militants killed and 2 injured on a strike on bakery in Miransha bazaar.
Up to 10 alleged militants killed and 4 injured in a double strike on a house in the village of Khassokhel.
2-4 alleged militants killed in a strike on a vehicle in Datta Khel.
Up to 4 killed, 2 alleged militants and possibly 2 civilians in a strike in a vehicle in Khawashi Khel.
Up to 10 killed and 7-10 injured in a strike on a house where a Taliban funeral took place. Possible civilian deaths.
Up to 18 alleged militants killed in a strike on a militant compound. Abu Yahya al-Libi, al Qaeda's effective number two, is believed to be amongst dead.
4 alleged militants killed in a strike on a vehicle traveling east from Miranshah.
Up to 4 alleged militants killed in a strike on a shop or house in Miranshah bazaar. AFP reports witness saying another instance of a follow-up strike.
At least 4 alleged militants killed when a CIA drone struck a house in the late evening. The strike was reportedly targeting alleged militants linked to Hafiz Gul Bahadur.
CIA drones struck a house killing up to eight people. The strike came around 7am, reportedly destroying the house.
In an evening strike, CIA drones struck a house killing at least 17. This was the first strike since Pakistan re-opened its borders to Nato convoys after a seven month diplomatic stand-off.
At least 9 were killed when up to 8 missile hit a compound alleged to belong to militant comander Sadiq Noor, ally of Hafiz Gul Bahadur.

Up to 7 alleged militants died when CIA drones fired 6 missiles at a house. 1 or 2 vehicles exploded. The attack took place hours after Pakistan ambassador to Washington again called for a halt to drone strikes.
At least 5 people killed as tribesmen gathered for Eid, declared early in Waziristan. One named militant was killed, and his wife. A house and car were hit in the attack.
Two vehicles were hit in an early morning strike, killing at least 4. The vehicles were reportedly traveling from Miranshah.
A further 2 people were killed when CIA drones returned, reportedly targeting the wreckage of the vehicles destroyed in the day's earlier strike (Ob286).

Badruddin Haqqani, son of the Haqqani leader and the network's senior military commander, may have been killed when up to 25 people died in a 7pm strike. Haqqani's son Osama may also have perished when drones hit a car and vehicle.
Up to 18 people were killed and up to 14 injured in a coordinated series of strikes that hit villages in the Shawal valley around noon. The strikes came 'minutes apart'.
Notes: 5 Reported killed only in this strike

Short Summary: In a second strike of the midday onslaught at least 4 were killed when CIA drones reportedly fired two missiles on a wall compound.
Notes: 4 reported killed only in this strike

Short Summary: In the third coordinated strike at least three people were killed.
Notes: 3 reported killed only in this strike

Short Summary: Attacks at 9am on a housing compound and a vehicle reportedly killed up to six people.

A car was destroyed when to missiles and three to four militants, possibly linked to Hafiz Gul Bahdur, were killed. This was the first strike in 20 days, and the first after protests over a blasphemous video left up to 17 dead.

Target: Abu Kasha al Iraqi, Saleh al Turki
Short Summary: At least 5 were killed, inlcuding senior al Qaeda member Abu Kasha al Iraqi, when two missiles destroyed a compound at around 9pm.00
A US drone strike reportedy targeted either a car or motorbike near Mir Ali in North Waziristan, killing up to four alleged militants.
A pre-dawn attack destroyed a compound belonging to Maulvi Abdullah, described as a local cleric, killing five alleged militants and injuring three more, according to reports.
Four missiles were reportedly fired at a madrassa belonging to Maulvi Shakirullah, killing up to 18 and wounding many more.
A woman and at least two others were killed when a drone hit a house and car. Militants and civilians were in the house according to military officers who said two children were injured.
A few hours after Taliban commander Maulvi Nazir was injured in a suicide bombing, up to 4 people were killed in a drone strike.
The second strike on the Shin Warsak area in three days reportedly killed Abdul Rehman al-Zaman Yemeni, described as 'a mid-level al Qaeda commander, equivalent to a colonel'.

Up to 11 were killed, reportedly including senior al Qaeda commander Sheikh Khalid Bin Abdul Rehman al Hussainan, in the first strike in North Waziristan for 43 days. The Prime Minster Pervez Ashraf complained to US ambassador Olson the same day.
Up to 4 were killed, including an alleged militant commander Mohammad Ahmed Almansoor. A compound and a car were destroyed in the strike.
At least three alleged militants were reported killed in a strike on a house near Mir Ali.
Up to five people were killed in a strike in the Shawal Valley area on the border of North and South Waziristan.
In one of their most significant strikes in recent years, CIA drones killed Maulvi Nazir, the powerful leader of the so-called 'good Taliban'.
A strike on a vehicle near Mir Ali, North Waziristan, reportedly killed four people.
Alleged TTP commander Wali Muhammad Mehsud - reportedly responsible for training suicide bombers - among the dead after as many as five CIA drones bombarded Babar Ghar.
Alleged al Qaeda deputy commander of militant training in Pakistan and Afghanistan killed in the first of twin strikes near Mir Ali
At least 2 killed in second strike, 15 minutes after the first near Mir Ali.
At least four killed in a strike on a motorcycle and house or compound.
CIA drones destroyed a house and killed at least 3. Between two and six missiles reportedly hit a building, which caught fire.
CIA drones destroyed a house, killing at least 4, in an area reportedly dominated by the TTP.
Drones kill at least one alleged militant, reportedly on horseback in North Waziristan. The horse reportedly died with its rider.
Either a house or vehicle was destroyed, killing at least three.
A house was destroyed and at least four people were killed - their bodies were burnt and they were unidentified.
A house was destroyed, killing alleged TTP or AQ militants. It hit the day after the president of ICRC criticised US drone strikes in Pakistan.
Wali Ur Rahman, second in command of the TTP, was killed in the first strike since a landmark speech.
At least 7 people killed, including a named local Taliban commander.
A CIA strike killed at least 16 people in a strike on a house in the early hours.
A drone strike killed at least two men on a motorbike, both purportedly "foreigners".
US drones killed at least five, either as they returned on foot from fighting in Afghanistan or as they broke the days Ramadan fasting with Iftar dinner.
Four alleged members of the Islamic Movement of Turkmenistan were killed by drones.
At least five alleged militants including three named militants killed in a night strike on a house.
At least six possibly foreign militants killed in the first strike in 16 days.
At least three died in the second strike in seven days.
The second strike in less than 24 hours killed at least four people.
The first strike for 31 days kills up to five, comes after Sharif visits Obama and asks for strikes to stop.
US drones killed Hakimullah Mehsud, leader of the TTP.
CIA killed at least 5 alleged Haqqani Network commanders in a strike on a madrassa outside the FATA.
A strike hit less than a day after opposition politicians claimed to have outed the CIA station chief in Islamabad.
The first ever US drone strike on Christmas day kills at least three in a house.
